---
description: Code change discipline
alwaysApply: true
---

Before editing code:
- Inspect the relevant existing files first.
- Prefer the smallest change that solves the task.
- Do not rewrite unrelated code.
- Do not introduce new dependencies unless there is a clear reason.
- Preserve existing behavior unless the task explicitly asks to change it.
- If a change affects data storage, migrations, environment variables, or scheduled jobs, call it out clearly after the edit.
- After editing, summarize what changed and mention any tests or checks run.